# Preserve Animations When Editing Content

When updating text, images, colors, or content in this project:

1. Inspect existing classes and `data-*` attributes before editing.
2. Identify which ones control animations, scroll effects, reveals, transitions, and JS behavior.
3. Replace only the inner content — preserve the animated structure around it.

Never remove unless the user explicitly asks:

- `data-text-reveal`, `data-reveal`, `data-reveal-section`, and related `data-reveal-*` attributes
- `mav-text-reveal`, `mav-reveal-item`, `is-visible` logic, and reveal spans
- Scroll animation hooks (`data-scroll`, `data-parallax`, locomotive listeners)
- Hover/transition classes used for motion
- IntersectionObserver / GSAP / ScrollTrigger hooks in JS

After content edits, verify the section animation still triggers on scroll.
